observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Agriculturist to undertake the following actions:
Conduct regular monitoring and prepare reports concerning the status of the breeding stocks;
Submit to the Municipal Accountant all necessary reports and supporting documents that will serve as the basis for the accurate recognition, valuation, and recording of Biological Assets, particularly for the proper accounting of any gains or losses arising from changes in asset value;
Secure a copy of the Project Proposal from the MSWD Officer and furnish the Municipal Accountant, along with other regular monitoring reports pertaining to the distributed breeding stocks, to ensure legal and documentary support for the program; and
Formulate and institutionalize a written policy or set of procedures governing the proper implementation and management of the LGU’s breeding program, in coordination with other relevant offices and personnel, to ensure consistency, accountability, and effective oversight.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to direct the:
BAC to hold a pre-procurement conference for procurement of goods with an ABC of more than ₱2,000,000.00, infrastructure projects with ABC of more than ₱5,000,000.00 and Consulting Services with ABC of more than ₱1,000,000.00, as this will determine the readiness of the agency in the procurement projects at hand in terms of legal, technical and financial requirements;
BAC and its TWG to invite the three observers of procurement activities within the prescribed period to promote transparency and allow their timely participation;
BAC through its Secretariat, to prepare and send the Notification of Bid Submission and ensure that the bidder receive the said document;
BAC and its TWG to judiciously conduct post-qualification by verifying, validating and ascertaining all statements made and documents submitted by the bidder with the LCB;
BAC to ensure that all posted PS are properly dated, and their validity periods comply fully with the requirements required by law;
TWG to ensure that the NOA will only be issued upon recommendation by BAC;
BAC Secretariat to post the NOA, NTP and the approved contracts in the PhilGEPS website within the prescribed period; and
BAC to ensure that all procurements made by the PE, under competitive bidding, strictly follow the proceedings and requirements of the bidding process.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
AAO to:
ensure strict compliance with Section 56 of RA 11975 by closely monitoring payroll deductions which can be achieved by maintaining individual ledgers per employee which will serve as a basis for evaluating and approving future loan applications to help prevent employees' NTHP from falling below the required minimum threshold and safeguard their financial well-being;
formulate internal policies and procedures governing the evaluation and approval of employees’ salary loan applications.  These should include a clear provision requiring the certification of NTHP as a mandatory requirement in the evaluation and approval of loans. Once drafted, should be submitted to the Municipal Mayor for review and approval;
refrain from issuing or signing certifications for loan applications in cases where an employee’s NTHP would fall below the minimum threshold of ₱5,000.00, exclusive of other loan obligations; and
Human Resource and Development Officer to conduct extensive information and awareness campaigns for all employees to ensure a comprehensive understanding of loan-related policies and requirements in order to empower employees with essential knowledge and promote financial literacy within the organization.

