We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

GSO-Designate to:

Prepare and maintain stock cards for each type of supplies and materials for monitoring the inventory levels;

Require from every requisitioning/end-user unit to submit a RIS before the issuance of the requested supplies and materials;

Prepare and submit on a weekly basis the required SSMI with the original copies of the RIS which would serve as the basis of the Municipal Accountant in recording expenses on supplies and materials in the books of accounts; and

Conduct inventory count on supplies and materials, with the assistance of the different departments of the Municipality, and incorporate the results of inventory count in the RPCI which will be submitted to the Municipal Accountant.

Municipal Accountant to:

Prepare and maintain SLC for each type of supplies and materials and reconcile the same regularly with the Stock Cards of the GSO – Designate;

Record the procurement of supplies and materials initially at their appropriate inventory accounts, and record the issuances of supplies and materials upon receipt of the SSMI with RIS; and

Obtain a copy of the RPCI which shall be her basis in identifying any discrepancies between the inventory count and recorded values of inventory items.

