observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Direct the BAC to intricately study and assess every procurement activity so that the mode of procurement that they recommend to be adopted is the proper mode to be undertaken;



Ensure that the BAC is kept abreast of the different procurement rules and regulations;



Enjoin concerned offices to read and study COA Circular 2012-001 and thereafter submit the required documents to the Auditor’s Office within five days from execution of the contract;

Order all implementing offices to monitor the due performance of every contractor of their obligations to the Municipality and timely initiate measures to avoid undue delays;



Devise a system of procedures for them to be able to appropriately act on requests for delivery extensions taking into consideration the Guidelines on Contract Implementation of the Generic Procurement Manual Volume II especially on making sure that extensions should only be granted if the grounds are meritorious; and



Ensure that the Municipality remains impartial in all of its dealings making sure that no particular party is given undue favour to the disadvantage of the government.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the following:

Municipal Engineer to impose liquidated damages on those remaining infrastructure projects and thereby submit supporting computation schedules;



Municipal Engineer to submit suspension orders, resumption orders and supporting documents corroborating the reasons provided therein;



Municipal Accountant impose the difference of ₱611,504.33 against the contractors; and



Municipal Accountant to defer final payment for those not yet imposed with liquidated damages.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:
derecognize the accumulated unsettled Accounts Payable amounting to ₱1,154,100.76, after due determination of its non-existence. Consider the existence of claims that were not forwarded in 2023 SL totaling ₱129,158.92;
derecognize the transactions recorded as AP totaling ₱1,933,740.00 but still include these under the Actual Amounts column of the SCBAA including the undeclared commitment of ₱3,782,331.27 and disclose the same as commitments in the notes to financial statements;
recognize Prior Period Adjustment for the following errors in recording: (a) settlement of unrecognized Accounts Payable; (b) settlement of Accounts Payable which should have been disclosed as commitment in prior year. Further, the comparative financial statements should be restated to effect the Prior Period Adjustments; and
submit the documents supporting the existence of recognized Accounts Payable totaling ₱7,585,192.85.

