In order to validate the accuracy, reliability, and completeness of the properties of the municipality as well as to establish the correct valuation, sufficient control and accountability for each property, we have recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the following:

GSO - Designate, with the assistance of the Municipal Engineer, to prepare the property cards, render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map, and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; 


Municipal Accountant update the property/supply ledger cards, subsidiary ledgers, AREs, and to prepare a disclosure of the gross carrying number of PPEs that are still in use or are still serviceable;




The members of the Inventory Committee to continuously conduct and complete the annual physical inventory, prepare the corresponding RPCPPE in accordance with the prescribed format the relevant information relative to the PPE and/or may seek assistance or coordinate with the department heads to make inventory of municipal properties in their respective offices, so as to address the manpower constraint in the conduct of physical count.

We have recommended that Management:

Judiciously plan PPAs related to DRRM and properly prepare a Disaster Risk Reduction Management Fund Plan, schedule the PPAs by considering the timeliness of their expected benefits;

Monitor the utilization of the LDRRM Fund focusing on PPAs requiring the highest priority in terms of urgency and/or impact on the areas of Disaster Risk Reduction and Management; 

Ensure efficient and effective implementation of all programmed projects identified during the year to optimize the utilization of the fund and to achieve the goals and objectives on disaster risk reduction and disaster preparedness-response capabilities; and

Incorporate fully the unexpended balance of the Special Trust Fund as of year-end in the LDRRMFIP so that the Fund could be utilized effectively for the benefit of the constituents.

